      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ingratiator</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard S Reade letter on James Traub's July 30 article praises US Senate candidate Rick Lazio's integrity6</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The main trait that makes Rick Lazio ''the anti-Hillary'' is his integrity, a term assiduously avoided by your writer, who, unable to skewer Lazio on his legislative record (Hillary Clinton has none), resorted to faint praise of his ''ingratiating'' and ''conciliatory'' personality.</p>
        <p>Lack of aggressiveness is not a character flaw; untruthfulness is.</p>
        <p>Richard S. Reade  Setauket, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
